"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Tonight we start off with a monologue about the Supreme Court and Obamacare.

JUDGE ANDREW NAPOLITANO is here to talk more about the recent Supreme Court decision holding up a specific part of Obamacare.

PETER SUDERMAN and CHRIS STIREWALT are here to continue to discuss the recent SCOTUS Obamacare ruling.

Tonight's panel consists of CARLEY SHIMKUS, ANDY LEVY, and BEN DOMENECH. First story on the docket - Trump polling well in Republican primary. (2nd place, wtf.)

Our panel returns to talk about the Confederate flag and the wandering iron sights of outrage. (Apple removes all confederate flag stuff - including any civil war game. The Jefferson memorial. Gone with the Wind.)

TOPICAL STORM:
Crocs are back.
Bobby Jindal is running for president - releases weird unproduced video.
Theater was supposed to show "Inside Out" but instead they showed "Insidious 3".
Arnold Schwarzenegger goes on Howard Stern - gets personal.
Llama spits in womans face.

Our intrepid panel returns. First up - IRS "accidentally" erased 400+ "backup tapes" which likely contained a couple hundred thousand emails. Emails which could have provided ammunition in the IRS targeting controversy. Michelle accidentally creates black market for students. Some have been caught selling salt, pepper, and sugar. Owners want to bury their pets with them.

AARON KELLY, writer of "Kelly Tough" is here to talk about her dad Jim Kelly and his struggle with cancer.

Nightcap. Mailbag.
